data.title: Prices match the quality
data.text: When you are paying $7 or $8 for a prepackaged sandwich or salad, it had better be damn good. Guess what, you get what you pay for here. The ingredients are fresh and healthy. Did I mention they have an enormous craft beer selection? I just read that back to myself and it sounds like I work there.

data.title: A cool little corner shop.
data.text: I have been here a few times now and usually get their sausage egg and cheese bisquit's.  They are quite good and not very costly. Good value. They have a good selection of sandwich's, salad's, snacks, soup's etc. Also a nice selection of micro-brew beers. Also they have some nice liquor bottle offering's too. The people who run this place are very nice also. Stop in and enjoy the cool vibes. Open late also.

data.title: From breakfast to late-night; great pop-in place
data.text: I've gotten breakfast from Pop-a-Top several times.  They operated in conjunction with several of the surrounding restaurants which are all locally owned and operated.  The biscuits were excellent and this morning, I tried one of their bagels with lemon garlic cream cheese.  All bagels are made at their sister shop across the street at the Wooly, and this one was fabulous.  Don't let the convenience store look through you off.  They have typical grab-and-go items, but there is more to this bodega than meets the eye.  Check it out some day!
